# 🧠 Questions and Answers – Day 3

## 1️⃣ Difference Between App, Object, Record, and Field

| Concept | Meaning |
|---|---|
| App | Collection of tabs and functionalities |
| Object | Database table |
| Record | Single data entry |
| Field | Stores specific information |

---

## 2️⃣ Standard vs Custom Objects

### Standard Objects
Objects already provided by Salesforce.

Examples:
- Account
- Contact
- Lead

---

### Custom Objects
Objects created according to business requirements.

Examples:
- Student
- Faculty
- Course

---

## 3️⃣ Why are Relationships Important?

Relationships connect objects and maintain structured enterprise data.

They help:
- Organize information
- Improve reporting
- Connect related records
- Maintain business workflows

---

## 4️⃣ Why should repetitive calculations be automated?

Automated calculations:
- Save time
- Improve accuracy
- Reduce human errors
- Increase efficiency

---

## 5️⃣ Why should invalid data be blocked early?

Blocking invalid data:
- Improves data quality
- Prevents incorrect records
- Maintains consistency
- Improves business reliability

---

## 6️⃣ Why do companies need structured data instead of spreadsheets?

Structured data helps companies:
- Manage large information efficiently
- Maintain relationships between records
- Improve reporting and analytics
- Scale enterprise systems easily

Spreadsheets become difficult to manage when business data becomes very large.
